cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.DB, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new compact data structure for the representation of LiDAR point clouds.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as LiDAR devices are commonly used in computer vision applications such as object detection and 3D reconstruction.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category as LiDAR point clouds are often used in graphics applications such as virtual reality and video game development.
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper discusses storage methods and indexing capabilities of LiDAR point cloud data.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss programming languages or frameworks used for processing and analyzing LiDAR point cloud data.
